{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":28329,"duration_api_ms":28303,"num_turns":2,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"cbba2d41-f16a-41a7-87b3-4436bffb4983","total_cost_usd":0.7586652500000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":105447,"cache_read_input_tokens":127113,"output_tokens":1442,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":105447,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":3,"outputTokens":1442,"cacheReadInputTokens":127113,"cacheCreationInputTokens":105447,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.7586652500000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 105 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures, 0 ignored) — verified by running cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes cleanly (no warnings)","model.rs:22-31 MilestoneId::new() correctly rejects dot-prefixed identifiers via starts_with('.'); the redundant == '.' and == '..' checks have been removed as they are subsumed by starts_with('.')","service.rs:111-123 TaskRunLineagePort::update_task_run now accepts started_at: DateTime<Utc> at line 119, enabling runless same-project retry disambiguation","service.rs:465-495 record_bead_completion now accepts started_at as a real parameter (line 477, not underscore-prefixed) and forwards it to update_task_run (line 490)","fs.rs:2558-2566 running_task_runs_for_bead filters by bead_id only (not project_id), enabling cross-project superseding of stale running attempts for the same bead","fs.rs:2823-2824 fail_superseded_running_attempt is now called unconditionally for any sole prior running attempt (not just legacy runless ones), supporting cross-project retry scenarios","fs.rs:2977-3038 runless update_task_run branch now narrows by started_at first (line 2981: entries[*index].started_at == started_at), preventing ambiguous matching when multiple runless retries exist for the same bead/project","Test runless_completion_replay_for_same_project_retry_repairs_journal (service.rs:3159-3283) verifies: two runless starts for same project, complete second, strip journal completion, replay completion with retry's started_at — asserts 1 BeadCompleted event and snapshot completed_beads=1, failed_beads=0","Test retry_start_on_same_bead_supersedes_running_attempt_from_other_project (service.rs:3534-3633) verifies: start bead-1/project-1/run-1, then start bead-1/project-2/run-2 — first attempt auto-failed with 'superseded by retry', second is Running, after completion snapshot shows Ready with completed_beads=1","All mutation paths (update_status, persist_plan, record_bead_start, update_task_run) remain under with_milestone_write_lock for serialized access","reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage rebuilds all counters from latest_task_runs_per_bead, preserves Paused status, transitions Active→Ready when no active beads remain"],"findings_or_gaps":["The outstanding risk — milestone mutations span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction — remains. All paths are serialized by the milestone mutation lock, replay-safe via started_at-based targeting, and auto-supersede stale running attempts, making this an acceptable trade-off for file-based storage.","AppError::RunStartFailed is still used (service.rs:549) for rejecting non-terminal outcomes in update_task_run, which is semantically a finalization rejection. A more specific error variant would be cleaner but this is cosmetic, not a correctness issue — carried forward from prior reviews.","The asymmetry between project-scoped idempotency check (find_matching_running_task_run filters by bead+project+run_id) and bead-scoped supersede check (running_task_runs_for_bead filters by bead only) is intentional for cross-project retry support but non-obvious to future maintainers. A brief inline comment at fs.rs:2823 explaining the rationale would help.","The active_bead_ids() function in model.rs:402-408 still contains its own internal latest_task_runs_per_bead() call while reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage computes latest runs separately. External callers of active_bead_ids would redundantly recompute, but this is minor and not a correctness concern."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"54f413a2-c3a4-4a3e-b931-c833549f13c6"}
